==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek ''satyr'', a mythological creature, as in a [[satyr play]].

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''satire'''
	the use of irony, sarcasm, ridicule, or the like, in exposing, denouncing, or deriding vice, folly, etc.

